				\begin{document}$10^{26}< Q<5\times 10^{27}~\text{s}^{-1}$\end{document} (approx. pre-perihelion January 2015 to May 2015 and post-perihelion December 2015 to April 2016) is characterized by an interplay of fluid effects and finite ion gyroradius effects and gives rise to a host of new phenomena never explored before. The weakly active stage with Q<1026s−1\documentclass[12pt]{minimal}
				\usepackage{amsmath}
				\usepackage{wasysym}
				\usepackage{amsfonts}
				\usepackage{amssymb}
				\usepackage{amsbsy}
				\usepackage{mathrsfs}
