In contrast to previous fly-by missions (e.g., Curdt et al. 1988, for Giotto), which mainly explored the outer coma and the inner coma to a lesser extent, Rosetta was orbiting 67P in the inner coma. For instance, Balsiger et al. (1986) showed that the plasma number density exhibit a 1/r\documentclass[12pt]{minimal}
