Overall, when accounting for the radial cometocentric dependence of the warm population, the densities of both populations increased with decreasing heliocentric distance, as might be expected when both the photo-ionisation frequency and neutral gas density increased. The density of the warm population increased from about 30 to 100cm−3\documentclass[12pt]{minimal}
