As well as emissions from dissociative excitation, photodissociation of cometary molecules generates emissions in the FUV. These are modelled as discussed in Stephenson et al. (2021). Measurements of the solar photon flux by TIMED/SEE orbiting the Earth is extrapolated to the position of 67P assuming a 1/rh2\documentclass[12pt]{minimal}
