				\usepackage{amsbsy}
				\usepackage{mathrsfs}
				\usepackage{upgreek}
				\setlength{\oddsidemargin}{-69pt}
				\begin{document}$-20~\text{V}$\end{document}. The boundary between the two regions appears in some crossings to be sharp, such as on 15 October, while at other points to be broad. The sharp boundary crossings likely appear to be sharp because the solar wind dynamic pressure increased due to an event such as a CIR or CME, causing the boundary to move across the spacecraft (see Mandt et al. 2016, for details). From Mandt et al. (2019), reproduced with permission ©ESO

