However, as reported in Goetz et al. (2016a,b) clear signatures of a magnetic field free region could be observed at 67P by Rosetta. It should be noted here, that the offset of the magnetometer was in the order of a couple of nT and thus in the initial data, the field was not observed as zero, instead the signatures were recognisable by a conspicuous absence of all field fluctuations that are predominant in the magnetic field around 67P close to perihelion (see Sect. 2.3.7). Assuming the field to be zero in the cavity has served as a good way to recalibrate the instrument, but on the other hand the exact field value in the cavity is only constrained to ±3nT\documentclass[12pt]{minimal}
